This paper is about a new compiler framework for deep learning models, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on the development of a compiler for deep learning models. The next likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as deep learning is a subfield of AI. The paper also discusses computer vision models, which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as another likely category. Additionally, the paper mentions the design of domain-specific optimizations, which could fall under cs.PL (Programming Languages) or cs.AR (Architecture).
